         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Incident Management Training and Exercising and Business Continuity Management</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>Project_21934</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Environment Agency is a Category 1 Responder organisation (as defined within the Civil Contingencies Act 2004). We require Incident Management Training delivery — Design and delivery of bespoke training to build knowledge, skills and capabilities,Develop of materials to support new ways of working and new tools as they develop, Consultancy in relation to training development and delivery.</P>
               <P>— Exercising: Design and develop exercising material to maintain levels of preparedness, Facilitation, Consultancy in relation to exercising development and delivery,</P>
               <P>— Business Continuity: Provision of Business Continuity advice into design and delivery working with the Training and Exercising suppliers, Delivery of Business Continuity training and exercising in its own right, Advising the organisation on its Business Continuity Plans.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">1800000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <LOT_DIVISION>
               <LOT_ALL/>
            </LOT_DIVISION>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Incident Management Training</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>1</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>We are looking for new approaches to ensure our staff are capable and confident in their roles. The training needs to cover Tactical, Operational and Strategic roles. These roles mirror our command and control structure which is used throughout. Category 1 and 2 multi-agency arena (across the board).</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="GBP">1100000.00</VAL_OBJECT>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">48</DURATION>
               <NO_RENEWAL/>
               <NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>5</NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>
               <CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
                  <P>Please refer to https://defra.bravosolution.co.uk and access the Supplier Selection Criteria documents for criteria.</P>
               </CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="2">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Exercising</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>2</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>This lot is concerned with putting the training into practice and testing our response structures, models, plans and procedures. Response plans may vary by area however we will publish Major Incident Plans (MIPS) as part of the tender to provide context to our requirements.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="GBP">530000.00</VAL_OBJECT>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">48</DURATION>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>Framework will be awarded for an initial period of 24 months with the option to extend for a further 24 months.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>3</NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>
               <CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
                  <P>Please refer to the supplier selection criteria for Lot 2 on https://defra.bravosolution.co.uk</P>
               </CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="3">
               <TITLE>
                  <P>Business Continuity Management (BCM)</P>
               </TITLE>
               <LOT_NO>3</LOT_NO>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>These requirements are varied in that we will require the successful supplier to work with the training and exercising suppliers as well as development and training on BCM in its own right. We will use the Lot 3 supplier to provide advice on and test our BCM structures and procedures.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="GBP">170000.00</VAL_OBJECT>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">48</DURATION>
               <RENEWAL/>
               <RENEWAL_DESCR>
                  <P>Framework period is initially 24 months with option to extend for a further 24 month period.</P>
               </RENEWAL_DESCR>
               <NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>3</NB_MAX_LIMIT_CANDIDATE>
               <CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
                  <P>Please refer to the SSC criteria for LOT 3 on: https://defra.bravosolution.co.uk</P>
               </CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
               <NO_ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
